[0m[49m[39m  155, 161[0m:[39m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[39m  156, 162[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  157, 163[0m:[39m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[39m  158, 164[0m:[39m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[39m  159, 165[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon Neptune** | Stores and queries clinical pathway graph structures |
[0m[49m[39m  160, 166[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Executes traversal logic, state updates, and compliance aggregation |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 161     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Maintains per-patient pathway state (current position, timestamps, completed steps) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Maintains per-patient pathway state (current position, timestamps, completed steps). GSI on `status` for efficient overdue checking. |
[0m[49m[39m  162, 168[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon EventBridge** | Routes clinical events (lab results, orders, assessments) to state update functions |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SQS** | Dead letter queue for failed clinical event processing |
[0m[49m[39m  163, 170[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Stores versioned pathway definitions and audit snapshots |
[0m[49m[39m  164, 171[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon QuickSight** | Visualizes pathway compliance metrics and variance patterns |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 165     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Manages encryption keys for Neptune, DynamoDB, and S3 |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 166     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Monitors traversal latency, state update throughput, and error rates |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Manages encryption keys (CMK with annual rotation) for Neptune, DynamoDB, and S3 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Monitors traversal latency, state update throughput, error rates, and DLQ depth alarms |
[0m[49m[39m  167, 174[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  168, 175[0m:[39m[49m ### Code
[0m[49m[39m  169, 176[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  170, 177[0m:[39m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[39m  171, 178[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  172, 179[0m:[39m[49m **Step 1: Model the pathway as a graph.** Before any code runs, you need to represent a clinical pathway as a graph structure that Neptune can store and traverse. Each pathway becomes a collection of nodes (clinical steps) connected by edges (transitions). The key design decision is how much clinical logic lives in the graph versus in the traversal code. Put conditions on edges as structured properties; put step metadata on nodes. This separation means the graph is queryable without external logic for simple traversals, but complex condition evaluation (pulling live patient data) happens in the Lambda layer. Skip this step or model it poorly, and every downstream query becomes a nightmare of application-side filtering.
[0m[49m[39m  173, 180[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  174, 181[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  175, 182[0m:[39m[49m // Define the pathway graph schema.
[0m[49m[39m  176, 183[0m:[39m[49m // Each node represents a clinical step or decision point.
[0m[49m[39m  177, 184[0m:[39m[49m // Each edge represents a valid transition with conditions.
[0m[49m[39m  178, 185[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  179, 186[0m:[39m[49m STRUCTURE PathwayNode:
[0m[49m[39m  180, 187[0m:[39m[49m     id:               unique identifier (e.g., "pneumonia-v3-step-004")
[0m[49m[39m  181, 188[0m:[39m[49m     pathway_id:       which pathway this belongs to
[0m[49m[39m  182, 189[0m:[39m[49m     pathway_version:  version number (pathways evolve over time)
[0m[49m[39m  183, 190[0m:[39m[49m     node_type:        one of [assessment, order, decision_point, milestone, discharge_criterion]
[0m[49m[39m  184, 191[0m:[39m[49m     name:             human-readable step name (e.g., "Calculate CURB-65 Score")
[0m[49m[39m  185, 192[0m:[39m[49m     description:      clinical description of what this step involves
[0m[49m[39m  186, 193[0m:[39m[49m     responsible_role: who performs this (physician, nurse, pharmacist, respiratory_therapy)
[0m[49m[39m  187, 194[0m:[39m[49m     expected_duration_hours: how long this step typically takes (null if instantaneous)
[0m[49m[39m  188, 195[0m:[39m[49m     required_documentation: what must be documented to mark this step complete
[0m[49m[39m  189, 196[0m:[39m[49m     parallel_group:   identifier for steps that can execute simultaneously (null if sequential)
[0m[49m[39m  190, 197[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  191, 198[0m:[39m[49m STRUCTURE PathwayEdge:
[0m[49m[39m  192, 199[0m:[39m[49m     from_node:        source node ID
[0m[49m[39m  193, 200[0m:[39m[49m     to_node:          target node ID
[0m[49m[39m  194, 201[0m:[39m[49m     edge_type:        one of [sequential, conditional, time_gated, parallel_start, parallel_join]
[0m[49m[39m  195, 202[0m:[39m[49m     conditions:       list of Condition objects that must ALL be true for this transition
[0m[49m[39m  196, 203[0m:[39m[49m     priority:         for conditional edges from same node, evaluation order (lower = first)
[0m[49m[39m  197, 204[0m:[39m[49m     max_time_hours:   if set, this transition becomes "overdue" after this many hours
[0m[49m[39m  198, 205[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  199, 206[0m:[39m[49m STRUCTURE Condition:
[0m[49m[39m  200, 207[0m:[39m[49m     condition_type:   one of [lab_value, vital_sign, elapsed_time, assessment_complete,
[0m[49m[39m  201, 208[0m:[39m[49m                               order_placed, allergy_check, diagnosis_present]
[0m[49m[39m  202, 209[0m:[39m[49m     parameter:        what to check (e.g., LOINC code for lab, vital sign name)
[0m[49m[39m  203, 210[0m:[39m[49m     operator:         one of [gt, gte, lt, lte, eq, neq, exists, not_exists]
[0m[49m[39m  204, 211[0m:[39m[49m     value:            threshold or expected value
[0m[49m[39m  205, 212[0m:[39m[49m     time_window_hours: how recent the data must be (null = any time)
[0m[49m[39m  206, 213[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  207, 214[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  208, 215[0m:[39m[49m **Step 2: Load pathway into Neptune.** Once you have the pathway modeled as structured data, load it into Neptune as a property graph. Each PathwayNode becomes a vertex with properties. Each PathwayEdge becomes an edge with properties. Conditions are stored as JSON properties on edges (for simple conditions) or as separate vertices linked to edges (for complex, reusable conditions). The loading process should validate graph integrity: every edge references existing nodes, every decision point has at least two outgoing conditional edges, and every pathway has exactly one start node and at least one terminal node.
[0m[49m[39m  209, 216[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  210, 217[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  211, 218[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION load_pathway_to_neptune(pathway_definition):
[0m[49m[39m  212, 219[0m:[39m[49m     // Validate the pathway graph structure before loading.
[0m[49m[39m  213, 220[0m:[39m[49m     // Catch structural errors here rather than discovering them at query time.
[0m[49m[39m  214, 221[0m:[39m[49m     VALIDATE:
[0m[49m[39m  215, 222[0m:[39m[49m         - exactly one node with node_type = "start"
[0m[49m[39m  216, 223[0m:[39m[49m         - at least one node with node_type = "discharge_criterion" or "terminal"
[0m[49m[39m  217, 224[0m:[39m[49m         - every decision_point node has >= 2 outgoing conditional edges
[0m[49m[39m  218, 225[0m:[39m[49m         - no orphan nodes (every node reachable from start)
[0m[49m[39m  219, 226[0m:[39m[49m         - no dangling edges (both endpoints exist)
[0m[49m[39m  220, 227[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  221, 228[0m:[39m[49m     // Create vertices for each pathway node.
[0m[49m[39m  222, 229[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each node in pathway_definition.nodes:
[0m[49m[39m  223, 230[0m:[39m[49m         ADD VERTEX to Neptune with:
[0m[49m[39m  224, 231[0m:[39m[49m             label     = node.node_type
[0m[49m[39m  225, 232[0m:[39m[49m             id        = node.id
[0m[49m[39m  226, 233[0m:[39m[49m             properties = {
[0m[49m[39m  227, 234[0m:[39m[49m                 pathway_id:       node.pathway_id,
[0m[49m[39m  228, 235[0m:[39m[49m                 pathway_version:  node.pathway_version,
[0m[49m[39m  229, 236[0m:[39m[49m                 name:             node.name,
[0m[49m[39m  230, 237[0m:[39m[49m                 description:      node.description,
[0m[49m[39m  231, 238[0m:[39m[49m                 responsible_role: node.responsible_role,
[0m[49m[39m  232, 239[0m:[39m[49m                 expected_duration_hours: node.expected_duration_hours,
[0m[49m[39m  233, 240[0m:[39m[49m                 parallel_group:   node.parallel_group
[0m[49m[39m  234, 241[0m:[39m[49m             }
[0m[49m[39m  235, 242[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  236, 243[0m:[39m[49m     // Create edges for each transition.
[0m[49m[39m  237, 244[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each edge in pathway_definition.edges:
[0m[49m[39m  238, 245[0m:[39m[49m         ADD EDGE to Neptune from edge.from_node to edge.to_node with:
[0m[49m[39m  239, 246[0m:[39m[49m             label      = edge.edge_type
[0m[49m[39m  240, 247[0m:[39m[49m             properties = {
[0m[49m[39m  241, 248[0m:[39m[49m                 conditions:     serialize(edge.conditions) as JSON,
[0m[49m[39m  242, 249[0m:[39m[49m                 priority:       edge.priority,
[0m[49m[39m  243, 250[0m:[39m[49m                 max_time_hours: edge.max_time_hours
[0m[49m[39m  244, 251[0m:[39m[49m             }
[0m[49m[39m  245, 252[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  246, 253[0m:[39m[49m     // Store the full pathway definition in S3 for versioning and audit.
[0m[49m[39m  247, 254[0m:[39m[49m     WRITE pathway_definition to S3 at:
[0m[49m[39m  248, 255[0m:[39m[49m         bucket: "clinical-pathways"
[0m[49m[39m  249, 256[0m:[39m[49m         key:    "{pathway_id}/v{pathway_version}/definition.json"
[0m[49m[39m  250, 257[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  251, 258[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  252, 259[0m:[39m[49m **Step 3: Map patient to pathway position.** When a patient is enrolled on a pathway (either manually by a clinician or automatically based on admission diagnosis), the system needs to track their current position. This means determining which node(s) they currently occupy. A patient can be at multiple nodes simultaneously if the pathway has parallel branches. The state record in DynamoDB captures: which nodes are active, when each was entered, and which nodes have been completed.
[0m[49m[39m  253, 260[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  254, 261[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  255, 262[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION initialize_patient_on_pathway(patient_id, pathway_id, pathway_version):
[0m[49m[39m  256, 263[0m:[39m[49m     // Find the start node for this pathway version.
[0m[49m[39m  257, 264[0m:[39m[49m     start_node = QUERY Neptune:
[0m[49m[39m  258, 265[0m:[39m[49m         "Find vertex where pathway_id = {pathway_id}
[0m[49m[39m  259, 266[0m:[39m[49m          AND pathway_version = {pathway_version}
[0m[49m[39m  260, 267[0m:[39m[49m          AND label = 'start'"
[0m[49m[39m  261, 268[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  262, 269[0m:[39m[49m     // Create the patient's pathway state record in DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[39m  263, 270[0m:[39m[49m     // This record will be updated every time a clinical event advances the patient.
[0m[49m[39m  264, 271[0m:[39m[49m     WRITE to DynamoDB table "patient-pathway-state":
[0m[49m[39m  265, 272[0m:[39m[49m         partition_key = patient_id
[0m[49m[39m  266, 273[0m:[39m[49m         sort_key      = pathway_id
[0m[49m[39m  267, 274[0m:[39m[49m         attributes    = {
[0m[49m[39m  268, 275[0m:[39m[49m             pathway_version:   pathway_version,
[0m[49m[39m  269, 276[0m:[39m[49m             enrolled_at:       current UTC timestamp,
[0m[49m[39m  270, 277[0m:[39m[49m             active_nodes:      [start_node.id],          // currently at the start
[0m[49m[39m  271, 278[0m:[39m[49m             node_entry_times:  {start_node.id: current UTC timestamp},
[0m[49m[39m  272, 279[0m:[39m[49m             completed_nodes:   [],                        // nothing completed yet
[0m[49m[39m  273, 280[0m:[39m[49m             completed_edges:   [],                        // no transitions taken yet
[0m[49m[39m  274, 281[0m:[39m[49m             status:            "active"                   // active, completed, or withdrawn
[0m[49m[39m  275, 282[0m:[39m[49m         }
[0m[49m[39m  276, 283[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  277, 284[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION advance_patient_state(patient_id, pathway_id, completed_node_id, next_node_id):
[0m[49m[39m  278, 285[0m:[39m[49m     // Called when a transition is confirmed (conditions met, action taken).
[0m[49m[39m  279, 286[0m:[39m[49m     // Atomically updates the patient's position on the pathway.
[0m[49m[39m  280, 287[0m:[39m[49m     UPDATE DynamoDB record for (patient_id, pathway_id):
[0m[49m[39m  281, 288[0m:[39m[49m         REMOVE completed_node_id from active_nodes
[0m[49m[39m  282, 289[0m:[39m[49m         ADD next_node_id to active_nodes
[0m[49m[39m  283, 290[0m:[39m[49m         ADD completed_node_id to completed_nodes
